It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. This is the last room in the house that has only been simply decorated.
Tear out the ugly electric fireplace and hearth. Seal the chimney, replace the cracked plaster, and repaint it. Get a custom closet.
We usually start with a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
A few dead birds were found behind the flue, their bodies completely dried out :(
Prepare to meet next week's plasterer
对旁边的嵌入式壁龛很满意
We're going to put in the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing it yet🙈)
Haha, what did we find behind the radiator! 😄
还记得加装了可爱的小通风口，防止烟囱受潮
Sweep 把烟囱盖和烟囱帽都装好了。那些喜欢在烟囱里筑巢的白嘴鸦以后应该会更安全了🪺
The plasterer is done. We'll lay the flooring tomorrow!
The cork pads have been laid, and we even made a dusting accessory for the vacuum cleaner with toilet paper rolls. 😂
Part of the flooring has been prepared, so we can start laying it now. Let's have a cup of tea and take a break.
Yeah, we're moving pretty slowly today because we need to cut around the door frames to match seamlessly with the hallway (which is also getting new flooring), which is quite a hassle. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about this to me.
It's finally finished, but everything is in a mess! To make matters worse, the assembly instructions for the new bed are terrible. I can finally get a good night's sleep tonight!
There's still the corridor floor and baseboard to do. The decorators won't come for another month, so we're making do with bare plasterboard in the rooms for now.
I did a quick DIY job last night. I cut off part of the bottom of the door frame with a tenon saw and chisel so the floor can fit perfectly underneath.
The cork underlay for the corridor is also done.
We laid the corridor floor yesterday! This morning at 5, we got up early to go to Heathrow Airport to pick up package number one, then had a nap, and now we can finally start installing the baseboards. We'll fill the gaps once the glue dries.
